      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to regulatory submission metrics specified in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs required by FDA guidance for ASTM F1717 pedicle screw submissions. The QoIs are directly relevant to the COU and the regulatory decision. No surrogate or proxy QoIs are used."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "rationale": "The relevance of the validation activities to the broader clinical COU — including in vivo loading conditions, patient variability, and long-term fatigue behavior — was considered beyond the scope of the present static compression-bending submission. The assessment team notes that the validation domain (ASTM F1717 bench test) is narrower than the full clinical use envelope, but formal evaluation of this gap was deferred as it was judged to fall outside the regulatory submission requirements for this device class. No requiredLevel or achievedLevel has been assigned."
    }
